 each book. Offering a wide-ranging look at the creation and use of books, illustrated with hundreds of color images, this volume is itself an object of beauty.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBooksxHistory. 0aPrintingxHistory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aart, artist, curators, illustrations, bookmaker, lettering, binding materials, design, manuscripts, scrolls, paperbacks, library, digital, cultural history, photography, pictures, manufacture, Asia, Europe, North America, Russia, Bible.1 aAguirre, Mercedes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBachmann, Iris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDefrance, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerillo, Eyob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoumy, Mélodie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoyle, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Adrian S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallop, Annabel Teh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIgunma, Jana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJenkins, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Edmund M. B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKither, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLimper-Herz, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarks, P.J.M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/voca